                <h1>Mastering Background Focus Photography: Tips & Techniques</h1>
                <p>Background focus photography is a technique that emphasizes a subject by intentionally blurring the background. This creates a striking visual contrast, drawing the viewer's eye directly to the main focus. Using a wide aperture can achieve this effect, allowing for stunning portraits or product shots while maintaining clarity on the subject.</p>
